Let $T$ have coordinates $(r,s).$  Since the area of $\triangle POQ$ is three times the area of $\triangle TOP,$
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot 12 \cdot 9 = 3 \cdot \frac{1}{2} \cdot r \cdot s,\]so $rs = 18.$

Also, $T$ lies on the line $y = -\frac{3}{4} x + 9,$ so
\[s = -\frac{3}{4} r + 9.\]Hence, $r$ and $s$ satisfy
\begin{align*}
rs &= 18, \\
s &= -\frac{3}{4} r + 9.
\end{align*}From the second equation, $r = \frac{4}{3} (9 - s),$ so
\[\frac{4}{3} (9 - s) \cdot s = 18.\]This simplifies to $4s^2 - 36s + 54 = 0,$ which factors as $4(s - 3)(s - \frac{9}{2}) = 0.$  Since $s$ is positive, $s = 3.$  Then $r = 6,$ so $r + s = \boxed{9}.$

